Bank of America Merrill Lynch has appointed Dale Wood as head of corporate banking for South Africa, tasked with expanding the business in the region. Wood will join BAML next month from Rand Merchant Bank, where he was head of debt capital markets. Wood will be based in Johannesburg and report to Richard Gush, country executive for South Africa, and Darren Rickards, head of corporate banking for central and eastern Europe, the Middle East and Africa.